parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and loss of power can cause accidents, especially when driving on high-speed roads, and can lead to a loss of control of the vehicle.
The wind noise issue can be a distraction to the driver, potentially leading to decreased attention on the road and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Increasing wind noise coming from around the front two windows
especially at speeds of 65 mph and above
sounding like a referee blowing a whistle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission hesitation and slipping can cause the vehicle to lunge or jerk, leading to loss of control, accidents, or damage to the engine and transmission.
The transmission internal damage can lead to transmission failure, causing the vehicle to become inoperable, and potentially resulting in accidents or stranding the driver.
